**STRONGS:** H8121 שֶׁמֶשׁ "to SERVE" → sun serves || H3394 יָרֵחַ = permanence/faithfulness || H3556 כּוֹכָב "figuratively, a prince" || G2246,G4582,G792/G798 direct parallels

**ROSETTA STONE:** Gen 37:9-10 Joseph's dream → Jacob decodes: sun=father, moon=mother, stars=brothers. Scripture's OWN first interpretation = authority hierarchy

**CREATION FUNCTION:** Gen 1:16-18 sun/moon to H4475 RULE day/night, not just illuminate. Ps 136:7-9 repeats RULE verb

**HIERARCHY STRUCTURE:**
- SUN = supreme/primary authority (generates light/authority) - Ps 84:11 God=sun, Mal 4:2 Messiah=Sun, Mat 17:2 Jesus' face as sun
- MOON = derivative/reflective authority (NO light of own, reflects sun) - Ps 89:37 faithful witness
- STARS = individual subordinate authorities/princes - vary in glory (1Cor 15:41), can fall (Dan 8:10), wander (Jude 1:13), fight (Judg 5:20)

